FBIS4-58446 "drnes086yy_94028" FBIS-NES-94-086 Daily Report 4 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Arab-Israeli Talks Reportage on Pre-Ceremony Events, Negotiations Reportage on Pre-Ceremony Events, Negotiations 'Arafat Said `Not Ready' for Transfer TA0405134994 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1300 GMT 4 May 94 TA0405134994 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1300 GMT 4 May 94 Hebrew BFN [Ehud Ya'ari studio report from Cairo -- live] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The next central issue, if I may call it that, is the fact that last night -- and so far I have not heard that this has changed -- 'Arafat told the Americans, Rabin, and Mubarak that he is not ready to immediately send in a large police force into the Gaza Strip. Therefore, the implementation of the agreement in practice, the practical handing over of the keys, may last more than the seven days which were initially scheduled for the initial assumption of power by 'Arafat's forces in Rafah and Jericho.
